- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper evaluates the performance of two JIT compilers on a real-world benchmark suite, which is relevant to software engineering research. 
- cs.AR (Architecture): The paper discusses the experimental setup used to evaluate the benchmark suite, which includes hardware and software components, and is relevant to computer architecture research. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper discusses concurrency primitives and evaluates the performance of JIT compilers, which are relevant to distributed and parallel computing research. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): Although not the main focus of the paper, machine learning techniques could potentially be used to optimize the JIT compilers based on the benchmark suite results.
